1
00:01:34,860 --> 00:01:37,650
[Bloom Life]

2
00:01:38,850 --> 00:01:42,690
[2015]

3
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:51,810
Go ahead. Go ahead.

4
00:02:08,060 --> 00:02:09,000
Uncle Elishir.

5
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:11,970
Why are you playing Tobok again?

6
00:02:11,970 --> 00:02:14,130
Mom, can't you do something?

7
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:16,060
What are you holding?

8
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:16,940
Knucklebones.

9
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,840
They made a pact.

10
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,500
No matter when and where,

11
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,470
whoever fails to take out

12
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:21,730
his own knucklebone

13
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,290
has to give the other person a sheep.

14
00:02:23,290 --> 00:02:25,310
This game is called Tobok.

15
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:29,020
Three, two, one.

16
00:02:32,810 --> 00:02:33,930
Both of them keep their knucklebones

17
00:02:33,930 --> 00:02:35,250
with them at all times,

18
00:02:35,410 --> 00:02:37,300
so it's always a tie.

19
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:51,680
[Episode 5: The Beginning of
a Great Friendship]

20
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:56,250
Happy Eid al-Adha.

21
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,890
Come celebrate at our house later.

22
00:03:12,610 --> 00:03:13,350
How is it?

23
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:16,890
Not bad, right?

24
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:23,370
Let me tell you something.

25
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:24,300
I deleted

26
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,700
the dating application.

27
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,680
You'd delete

28
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:28,020
yours too.

29
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,180
It's okay that you've deleted yours.

30
00:03:30,180 --> 00:03:31,780
But don't interfere with me.

31
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,630
Just delete it.

32
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:34,630
Why?

33
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:36,530
Young man,

34
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:37,910
look at the clothes you're wearing.

35
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:38,870
It looks terrible.

36
00:03:38,870 --> 00:03:39,640
It's a festival.

37
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,090
You need to dress for the occasion.

38
00:03:41,090 --> 00:03:41,780
Adalanti,

39
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,200
bring a Kanawayi shirt.

40
00:03:47,350 --> 00:03:48,079
You're back.

41
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:57,130
Dad.

42
00:03:58,010 --> 00:03:58,600
Dad.

43
00:03:59,410 --> 00:04:01,540
Why is Mulading sharpening the knife?

44
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:04,980
We are distributing mutton
for the festival today.

45
00:04:05,130 --> 00:04:06,790
I asked Mulading to handle it.

46
00:04:06,890 --> 00:04:08,520
How could you let him do it?

47
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:10,290
Isn't it you and Uncle's work?

48
00:04:12,130 --> 00:04:12,810
Mulading

49
00:04:12,810 --> 00:04:15,060
will become my son-in-law soon.

50
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,440
Of course, he should handle it.

51
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:43,890
I'm here to return your bag.

52
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,800
I'll transfer the money to you.

53
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:53,230
No need.

54
00:04:53,690 --> 00:04:55,420
I already ate the pomegranate.

55
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:57,450
The pomegranate isn't worth much.

56
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:59,260
I broke your jar,
so I should pay you back.

57
00:04:59,260 --> 00:05:01,330
No need, really.

58
00:05:02,890 --> 00:05:03,370
But

59
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,770
could you do me a favor?

60
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:06,600
A favor?

61
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:08,480
What is it?

62
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:10,650
Do you have a girlfriend?

63
00:05:22,810 --> 00:05:24,810
Can you pretend to be my boyfriend?

64
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,560
Is that okay?

65
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,300
If it's too much trouble,

66
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,690
just forget it.

67
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:35,860
I...

68
00:05:35,890 --> 00:05:37,960
I can ask someone else.

69
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:40,210
It's really fine.

70
00:05:40,210 --> 00:05:42,260
I guess I could.

71
00:05:45,450 --> 00:05:46,570
So you agreed?

72
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:50,390
Okay.

73
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:55,620
I'm Parhat.

74
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:56,659
I'm Laili.

75
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:57,860
Laili.

76
00:06:11,730 --> 00:06:13,060
And this is Ying.

77
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,390
Ying.

78
00:06:26,370 --> 00:06:27,500
How did you do that?

79
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:34,550
No, I can't.

80
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:43,620
Uncle.

81
00:06:44,330 --> 00:06:45,680
Hello, Uncle.

82
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,870
Hello.

83
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:47,870
I brought some stuff.

84
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:48,930
Happy Eid al-Adha.

85
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:50,070
Wait.

86
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,060
Adalanti.

87
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:52,540
Get one more shirt.

88
00:06:52,540 --> 00:06:53,220
Get one more shirt.

89
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:54,000
Got it.

90
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,510
Shirt?

91
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:56,450
Hello.

92
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:03,920
Hello.

93
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:04,800
Hello.

94
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:29,510
Go, Grandma wants to give
you a red envelope.

95
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:32,710
Say thank you to Grandma.

96
00:07:32,730 --> 00:07:33,890
Happy Eid al-Adha. Thank you.

97
00:07:33,890 --> 00:07:35,600
Thank you, grandma.

98
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,620
Happy Eid al-Adha!

99
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:38,740
You have to dance
after receiving money.

100
00:07:38,740 --> 00:07:39,630
How? I don't know how to dance.

101
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:40,310
Just like this. Come on.

102
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,330
I can't dance.

103
00:07:41,659 --> 00:07:42,980
Follow the rhythm.

104
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,180
Come on.

105
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:47,340
Yes.

106
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:48,350
Dance like this.

107
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,060
Follow the rhythm.

108
00:07:53,659 --> 00:07:55,060
You are quite good at it.

109
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,500
I learned it just now.

110
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:58,440
Quite talented.

111
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,010
The mutton is cooked so well.

112
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:10,690
Auntie,

113
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,680
let Mulading distribute

114
00:08:12,810 --> 00:08:14,220
the mutton this year.

115
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:15,920
What do you think?

116
00:08:22,050 --> 00:08:23,110
Let me introduce

117
00:08:23,140 --> 00:08:24,820
my boyfriend, Parhatin.

118
00:08:25,450 --> 00:08:27,510
Hello everyone.

119
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,540
Hello.

120
00:08:31,220 --> 00:08:32,220
Take a seat first.

121
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,940
Hello, grandma.

122
00:08:36,150 --> 00:08:37,289
I picked him up on the road.

123
00:08:37,289 --> 00:08:38,549
Picked him up on the road?

124
00:08:38,549 --> 00:08:39,669
You picked up a boyfriend?

125
00:08:39,669 --> 00:08:41,789
You are quite bold, Little girl.

126
00:08:41,789 --> 00:08:42,530
Parhat.

127
00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:47,620
Adijiang's grandson?

128
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,370
Yes, grandma.

129
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:51,100
Adijiang is my grandfather.

130
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:55,130
Good boy. Drink tea and eat some snacks.

131
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,870
Asimjan.

132
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:57,870
Grandma.

133
00:08:57,910 --> 00:09:01,840
You distribute the mutton
to everyone today.

134
00:09:03,170 --> 00:09:03,810
Okay.

135
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:06,350
What did grandma say?

136
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:08,460
Grandma mistook you for Asimjan.

137
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,680
She asked you to distribute the mutton.

138
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:11,930
Grandma, I'm

139
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:12,460
Zhou.

140
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:16,210
Wearing this clothes, you look
exactly like

141
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,500
my Asimjan.

142
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,080
Who is Asimjan?

143
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:23,250
Laili's elder brother.

144
00:09:23,450 --> 00:09:25,110
He passed away many years ago.

145
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,510
Come, the mutton is ready.

146
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,630
Eat it while it's warm.

147
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:39,670
Eat it while it's warm, everyone.

148
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:42,190
Grandma, I will be responsible for
distributing the mutton this year.

149
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:42,850
Who are you?

150
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:43,390
Grandma.

151
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:47,850
How can you touch our family's mutton?

152
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:49,630
Grandma.

153
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:51,120
Don't misunderstand.

154
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:52,130
My mother is old.

155
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:52,890
Her eyesight is bad.

156
00:09:52,890 --> 00:09:54,440
She mistook him for someone else.

157
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,360
All right.

158
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,290
Come on.

159
00:09:56,290 --> 00:09:57,600
Come on, everyone, eat up.

160
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,150
Have some food.

161
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:01,240
Happy Eid al-Adha, everyone.

162
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:06,870
What's up?

163
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:08,550
I finally got a chance to come back.

164
00:10:08,550 --> 00:10:10,290
Why are you so unhappy?

165
00:10:10,290 --> 00:10:10,940
Am I not welcome?

166
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:12,340
No.

167
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,110
Minawar.

168
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:15,650
Why didn't Sadiq come?

169
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:17,270
I asked him to go to his own home.

170
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:18,390
And I came to mine.

171
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:19,550
It doesn't conflict.

172
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:21,010
I didn't let him follow me.

173
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,520
Nonsense.

174
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:23,750
Dad.

175
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,150
Everyone is here for the holiday.

176
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,270
Don't scold me.

177
00:10:26,270 --> 00:10:28,330
I'm hungry. Give me something to eat.

178
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:29,480
Minawar.

179
00:10:30,090 --> 00:10:32,150
Did your mother-in-law not feed you?

180
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,810
How did you get so thin?

181
00:10:34,340 --> 00:10:35,370
Really?

182
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:36,980
Really?

183
00:10:36,980 --> 00:10:38,530
Yes. You're slim now.

184
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:39,410
That's great.

185
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:41,410
Then, I won't hide it from everyone.

186
00:10:41,410 --> 00:10:43,070
I have good news for everyone.

187
00:10:43,370 --> 00:10:45,510
I'm going to play Sänäm in the troupe.

188
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:46,360
Sänäm!

189
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,130
Good!

190
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:51,480
Laili.

191
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:52,880
Is this your friend?

192
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:53,980
He's not my friend.

193
00:10:54,060 --> 00:10:56,060
He's my future husband and my family.

194
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:57,920
A lady shouldn't say that.

195
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:00,440
Shame on you!

196
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,750
How am I shameless?

197
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,440
You force me to marry every day.

198
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,550
Now that I've found a boyfriend.

199
00:11:04,550 --> 00:11:05,550
Why are you upset?

200
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:16,270
Master.

201
00:11:16,390 --> 00:11:17,650
Please don't be angry.

202
00:11:18,670 --> 00:11:19,290
It's fine,

203
00:11:20,110 --> 00:11:21,510
as long as Laili is happy.

204
00:11:22,170 --> 00:11:22,820
Bro.

205
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,240
Sit for a while.

206
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,670
I'll go pour you some more tea.

207
00:11:25,670 --> 00:11:26,370
Mulading.

208
00:11:26,980 --> 00:11:28,010
Sit down.

209
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,050
Laili.

210
00:11:31,270 --> 00:11:33,800
Mulading has been
in our family for ten years.

211
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,120
I raised him like a son.

212
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,600
He is your future husband.

213
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,940
He's not!

214
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:46,550
And he is not your son.

215
00:11:46,550 --> 00:11:47,880
My brother is long gone.

216
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,000
Batur.

217
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:56,460
Uncle.

218
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,250
Dad.

219
00:12:11,610 --> 00:12:13,280
Don't go back today.

220
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,180
Just stay here.

221
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,470
No, I still have to go back.

222
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:19,100
Or my dad won't be able to sleep.

223
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:22,930
Don't worry.

224
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:25,170
I'm not really mad at my dad.

225
00:12:25,410 --> 00:12:27,030
I'm just mad at myself.

226
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:29,780
I often think that,

227
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:31,840
back then,

228
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:33,410
if I hadn't

229
00:12:33,430 --> 00:12:35,230
asked my brother to feed the dog,

230
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:38,060
he wouldn't have been crushed
under the house.

231
00:12:39,430 --> 00:12:40,060
Then,

232
00:12:41,220 --> 00:12:43,940
our family wouldn't have lost hope.

233
00:12:44,290 --> 00:12:46,630
Maybe things wouldn't be like this now.

234
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:51,510
You think too much.

235
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:53,430
It's not your fault.

236
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:54,500
It's not your problem.

237
00:12:54,500 --> 00:12:55,770
I think it is my fault.

238
00:12:55,910 --> 00:12:57,340
No.

239
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:00,630
Coming.

240
00:13:01,620 --> 00:13:03,110
Coming.

241
00:13:02,590 --> 00:13:06,370
[Ten years ago]

242
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:09,170
My Asimjan has grown up too.

243
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,980
Let him distribute

244
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:13,630
this year's mutton to us.

245
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:14,480
Laili,

246
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:17,270
your favorite sheep tail fat
dipped in chili.

247
00:13:18,050 --> 00:13:19,650
My brother loves me the most.

248
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:26,820
Laili, I gave it a name,

249
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,170
Meat-buns.

250
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:30,050
Okay, it's chubby.

251
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:32,610
Let me hold it.

252
00:13:32,610 --> 00:13:33,150
No.

253
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:33,940
Let me hold it for a while.

254
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:34,390
No.

255
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,720
Come on, let me hold it for a bit.

256
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,480
Let me hold it.

257
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,750
Fine, here you go.

258
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:38,820
So cute.

259
00:13:40,130 --> 00:13:41,630
Look, brother.

260
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:43,630
I made a small bowl for it.

261
00:13:44,410 --> 00:13:46,670
Do you think Dad will
let it into the kiln?

262
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,420
Yes, I believe in you.

263
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,240
Then, you tell Dad to do it.

264
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,010
Slow down.

265
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:50,820
Goodbye.

266
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,820
Bye.

267
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:09,380
I'm leaving.

268
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:10,820
We'll walk you in.

269
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:11,720
No need.

270
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,470
We'll watch you go in before we leave.

271
00:14:13,470 --> 00:14:14,950
It's fine, I can go by myself.

272
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:16,000
Let's go.

273
00:14:21,220 --> 00:14:21,770
Let's go.

274
00:14:22,890 --> 00:14:23,750
We're leaving.

275
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:35,700
Are you

276
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,440
okay?

277
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,580
Actually,

278
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,030
I'm really sorry

279
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:41,890
for letting you

280
00:14:41,950 --> 00:14:43,380
see this scene.

281
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,440
I don't even know how to face you.

282
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:46,980
It's fine.

283
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:49,150
I just came to see how you are.

284
00:14:49,420 --> 00:14:50,670
I'm happy to see you're okay.

285
00:14:50,670 --> 00:14:51,340
Well,

286
00:14:52,530 --> 00:14:53,530
I'll leave first.

287
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:58,200
Thank you.

288
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:00,480
No problem.

289
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,480
If this happens again, just call me.

290
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:04,330
No,

291
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,400
that's not what I meant.

292
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,230
I mean,

293
00:15:06,940 --> 00:15:08,140
if you ever need help,

294
00:15:08,250 --> 00:15:09,650
you can always come to me.

295
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:19,370
-Bye.
-Bye.

296
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:21,840
Go inside.

297
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:46,550
I'm back.

298
00:15:47,350 --> 00:15:48,520
Why are you back so late?

299
00:15:48,520 --> 00:15:49,780
I'm starving to death.

300
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:56,080
Sadiq, let me tell you,

301
00:15:56,270 --> 00:15:58,650
the troupe leader finally
praised me today.

302
00:15:58,650 --> 00:15:59,710
-She said I…
-Good.

303
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:04,040
Can you pour me some water?

304
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:08,840
Sure.

305
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:28,790
Eat up.

306
00:16:35,010 --> 00:16:36,720
Can we eat less meat?

307
00:16:36,890 --> 00:16:38,350
The calories are too high.

308
00:16:38,510 --> 00:16:39,840
I want some vegetables.

309
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,120
I packed naan with mutton for you.

310
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,520
How is it not nutritious?

311
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:47,860
Isn't this mutton good?
It has fat and lean.

312
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:51,190
This onion can be seen as a vegetable too.

313
00:16:51,210 --> 00:16:51,780
Eat up.

314
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,100
I was too tired after work yesterday.

315
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:54,700
And

316
00:16:55,330 --> 00:16:56,580
there was a pile of unwashed dishes.

317
00:16:56,580 --> 00:16:58,500
You told me to leave them alone for now.

318
00:16:58,500 --> 00:16:59,750
I thought you would wash them.

319
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:01,550
But those dishes are still

320
00:17:01,550 --> 00:17:02,650
in the kitchen.

321
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,540
Let me ask you a question.

322
00:17:06,569 --> 00:17:08,250
Last month,

323
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:10,990
I wanted to get a new interior for my car.

324
00:17:10,990 --> 00:17:12,450
Did I ask you to do it for me?

325
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:13,599
No.

326
00:17:14,460 --> 00:17:15,180
Why?

327
00:17:17,310 --> 00:17:17,960
Because

328
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,160
that's your business.

329
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,810
And I don't know anything about that.

330
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:22,400
Exactly.

331
00:17:23,619 --> 00:17:25,119
I'm the one who couldn't
stand the old interior,

332
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:25,790
not you.

333
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:27,960
So I had to change it myself.

334
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:28,880
But think about it,

335
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,650
I don't mind leaving dirty dishes
there for two days,

336
00:17:30,650 --> 00:17:32,450
or even piling them up for a week.

337
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,830
When Auntie comes on the weekend,

338
00:17:33,830 --> 00:17:35,440
just let her wash them.

339
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,900
This mutton is pretty good. Have a taste.

340
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:45,920
What's up now?

341
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:47,720
Nothing.

342
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:58,070
What are you doing?

343
00:17:58,070 --> 00:17:59,190
You've been in there for ages.

344
00:17:59,190 --> 00:18:00,790
Wait a minute. I'm not done yet.

345
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:01,770
Hurry up.

346
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,210
What did you want to tell me?

347
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:19,940
Come here.

348
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:22,440
I'm pregnant.

349
00:18:24,610 --> 00:18:25,400
Really?

350
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,660
Laili, come here.

351
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,010
What's wrong?

352
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,120
She's pregnant.

353
00:18:32,310 --> 00:18:33,250
Really?

354
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,900
Would I joke about this?

355
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:36,880
What are you going to do?

356
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:39,140
Have the baby.

357
00:18:39,460 --> 00:18:41,680
I didn't know you liked kids so much.

358
00:18:42,830 --> 00:18:44,350
It's not that I like kids.

359
00:18:44,350 --> 00:18:45,010
I just think

360
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:47,570
getting married is for having kids.

361
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:50,190
I'd like to have them sooner
rather than later.

362
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,950
Are you ready to be a mother?

363
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:56,180
Here is what I think.

364
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,640
Nanny, check.

365
00:18:59,230 --> 00:19:00,170
Money, check.

366
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:01,510
Big house,

367
00:19:01,530 --> 00:19:01,990
check.

368
00:19:02,420 --> 00:19:03,960
No, I didn't mean money.

369
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:04,890
I mean,

370
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,680
what about Sänäm?

371
00:19:11,160 --> 00:19:12,690
You hit the nail on the head.

372
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:14,230
About this,

373
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:15,610
only

374
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,410
you two

375
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:17,220
and I know.

376
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:19,220
Do not let anyone else know it.

377
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,440
Sadiq and my mother-in-law

378
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,170
still don't know I'm pregnant.

379
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:25,610
If she finds out,

380
00:19:25,610 --> 00:19:27,460
she'll react.

381
00:19:28,940 --> 00:19:30,830
Did your mother-in-law
make things difficult for you?

382
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,940
Who could make things
difficult for me?

383
00:19:32,940 --> 00:19:34,400
Let me tell you something.

384
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:36,660
Last week, I got up at 8 a.m.,

385
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:38,590
and she hinted that I was lazy

386
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,590
and not diligent.

387
00:19:40,590 --> 00:19:41,660
Then, this week,

388
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:42,860
I got up at 6 a.m.

389
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,070
and bought breakfast for the whole family,

390
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:46,180
and she still complained

391
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:48,140
that food from outside isn't clean.

392
00:19:48,140 --> 00:19:49,570
She advised me to cook myself.

393
00:19:49,570 --> 00:19:50,790
How could she be so harsh?

394
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,250
Guess what time I woke up today?

395
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:52,850
What time?

396
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:55,090
4 o'clock? That early?

397
00:19:55,810 --> 00:19:56,810
Before dawn,

398
00:19:56,810 --> 00:19:58,270
I got up for the whole family

399
00:19:58,270 --> 00:19:59,780
to make dough and bake naan.

400
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:01,780
As expected, she had nothing to say.

401
00:20:02,220 --> 00:20:03,790
Isn't it just playing the role of
a good daughter-in-law?

402
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:05,000
What's so hard about it?

403
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,610
As long as I want to do it,

404
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:08,300
there's nothing I can't do.

405
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,460
I have a performance in a month.

406
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,980
Once I put on that baggy costume,

407
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:17,240
who will be able to tell I'm pregnant?

408
00:20:18,850 --> 00:20:20,650
Cheer up. Have some pistachios.

409
00:20:21,090 --> 00:20:22,350
I'll go clean up first.

410
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:30,860
She has morning sickness.

411
00:20:32,270 --> 00:20:32,860
Get this.

412
00:20:33,220 --> 00:20:33,900
Come on.

413
00:20:34,620 --> 00:20:36,180
Watch your hair.

414
00:20:36,590 --> 00:20:37,050
Come on.

415
00:20:39,730 --> 00:20:40,770
Nothing came out.

416
00:20:45,020 --> 00:20:46,780
Why do I feel sick eating this?

417
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:49,330
-Do you want something sour?
-I'll remove it.

418
00:21:02,330 --> 00:21:03,350
Congratulations.

419
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:04,880
You're going to be a mother.

420
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:12,940
Thank you guys.

421
00:21:20,310 --> 00:21:21,570
I'll be the godmother.

422
00:21:21,970 --> 00:21:23,500
We will both be godmothers.

423
00:21:26,450 --> 00:21:29,270
Accompanying Minawar
as she becomes a mother,

424
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:32,160
I share her fears,

425
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:33,580
scares,

426
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:35,520
and nervousness.

427
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,440
I can't imagine

428
00:21:38,990 --> 00:21:41,250
that in the process of becoming a mother,

429
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,000
a woman's body

430
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,620
can house a brand new life.

431
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,370
At the same time,

432
00:21:49,420 --> 00:21:50,830
we are also excited,

433
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,180
joyful,

434
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,250
and looking forward to this new life.

435
00:21:56,010 --> 00:21:57,480
This is truly an adventure

436
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,720
and a journey full of surprises.

437
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:06,400
I brought some food.

438
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:07,930
Have a few bites before you go.

439
00:22:07,930 --> 00:22:10,130
What delicious food did you make for me?

440
00:22:10,790 --> 00:22:11,350
Eat some.

441
00:22:11,570 --> 00:22:12,700
Thin-skinned buns.

442
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:13,980
I made them myself.

443
00:22:14,450 --> 00:22:15,330
You made them?

444
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,070
Try them.

445
00:22:21,030 --> 00:22:22,000
Good for you.

446
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:23,800
I'll save some

447
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:26,710
to give to your dad
and trick him into thinking I made them.

448
00:22:26,710 --> 00:22:28,850
I can just make some more for him.

449
00:22:29,460 --> 00:22:31,170
Look at your little tricks.

450
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:37,600
Mom.

451
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:41,060
I'm not planning to go back to Shanghai.

452
00:22:48,350 --> 00:22:49,550
You're grown-up now.

453
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,330
Just bear the consequences

454
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:52,880
of your choice.

455
00:22:57,140 --> 00:22:58,240
I think

456
00:22:59,070 --> 00:23:00,270
I should retire.

457
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,680
When I first came here,

458
00:23:04,010 --> 00:23:07,660
this hospital didn't even have a decent
traditional Chinese medicine doctor.

459
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:10,590
I built this department from scratch.

460
00:23:10,810 --> 00:23:13,550
Now, it has over a dozen

461
00:23:15,390 --> 00:23:18,310
local doctors.

462
00:23:19,220 --> 00:23:21,460
They can all stand on their own now.

463
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:23,910
I think I can leave with peace of mind.

464
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:30,070
Can you bear to leave it?

465
00:23:31,140 --> 00:23:32,900
I also have to consider

466
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:34,940
how to spend the rest of my life.

467
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:39,900
That's great.

468
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,440
I'm happy for you.

469
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:45,940
Mom.

470
00:23:47,180 --> 00:23:49,240
How did you feel

471
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:51,630
when you were pregnant with me?

472
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:54,510
What's wrong?

473
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:58,050
When I was pregnant with you,

474
00:23:58,300 --> 00:24:01,160
it was the busiest time
setting up this department.

475
00:24:01,290 --> 00:24:03,460
I threw up every day
for the first three months.

476
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:04,610
Really, every single day.

477
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:06,610
I threw up like crazy.

478
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:09,180
When it came to the sixth month,

479
00:24:09,180 --> 00:24:10,610
I remember it clearly,

480
00:24:10,940 --> 00:24:12,110
you

481
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,460
finally made peace with me.

482
00:24:15,090 --> 00:24:16,940
I'm sorry, Mom.

483
00:24:17,650 --> 00:24:19,600
Coming to aid Xinjiang while pregnant

484
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,000
gave me a lot of pressure.

485
00:24:22,050 --> 00:24:25,240
At that time, all your grandparents

486
00:24:26,010 --> 00:24:26,940
were against it.

487
00:24:28,110 --> 00:24:29,240
I was thinking

488
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:31,300
maybe I'd stay for three or four years

489
00:24:31,820 --> 00:24:33,260
to set up this department

490
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:35,810
and go back once it was on track.

491
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,530
But once I stayed here,

492
00:24:42,330 --> 00:24:43,990
I fell in love with this place.

493
00:24:44,330 --> 00:24:45,730
I couldn't bear to leave.

494
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:51,200
Besides, seeing you so happy here,

495
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:52,900
so free,

496
00:24:52,900 --> 00:24:54,110
and so carefree

497
00:24:55,010 --> 00:24:57,610
I strengthened my determination
to stay here.

498
00:24:59,770 --> 00:25:01,030
I should thank you.

499
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:03,640
Because of you,

500
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,500
I became who I am today.

501
00:25:05,880 --> 00:25:08,160
I should thank you even more.

502
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:12,140
Let's thank each other.

503
00:25:32,250 --> 00:25:33,700
Is this your cat?

504
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:34,660
Yes.

505
00:25:37,050 --> 00:25:39,180
How have you been lately?

506
00:25:39,180 --> 00:25:41,090
How could I be?

507
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,420
Pretty good.

508
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:46,830
Come on, kids.

509
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:47,790
Eat some apricots.

510
00:25:47,790 --> 00:25:49,660
I just picked them from the orchard.

511
00:25:49,660 --> 00:25:51,260
I was just craving apricots.

512
00:25:51,460 --> 00:25:53,330
Ah, our cat

513
00:25:53,330 --> 00:25:55,020
is usually afraid of strangers.

514
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:55,700
Come here.

515
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,080
Come here.

516
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:58,790
This is my grandpa.

517
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:00,810
Hello, grandpa.

518
00:26:00,810 --> 00:26:02,020
Hello, child.

519
00:26:02,250 --> 00:26:03,640
Laili, my friend.

520
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:06,290
Okay.

521
00:26:06,610 --> 00:26:07,220
Let's go.

522
00:26:07,220 --> 00:26:08,030
Go home.

523
00:26:08,230 --> 00:26:09,050
Be a good boy.

524
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,980
This is what I want to mail.

525
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:14,150
I was going to charge you five yuan,

526
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:15,960
but I won't charge your family anymore

527
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:17,090
since you helped me.

528
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,240
Thanks.

529
00:26:21,010 --> 00:26:23,500
By the way, there's something

530
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,760
I came here to tell you.

531
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:27,370
You don't need to

532
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:29,380
pretend to be my boyfriend anymore.

533
00:26:30,770 --> 00:26:32,570
Sorry for the trouble last time.

534
00:26:41,660 --> 00:26:42,450
Parhat.

535
00:26:44,810 --> 00:26:45,960
I was just thinking,

536
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:49,660
if your dad knows you
don't have a boyfriend,

537
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:52,670
wouldn't he still force you
to marry Mulading?

538
00:26:52,670 --> 00:26:54,900
Then, all the things we did before...

539
00:26:57,460 --> 00:26:58,250
Then...

540
00:26:59,420 --> 00:27:01,000
Then, how about

541
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:05,850
I trouble you for a bit longer?

542
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,180
It's okay.

543
00:27:08,180 --> 00:27:09,140
What did you...

544
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:15,270
Have one.

545
00:27:54,630 --> 00:27:56,760
♪ Miss. My lady ♪

546
00:27:56,790 --> 00:27:58,650
♪ Follow me ♪

547
00:27:58,960 --> 00:28:01,160
♪ Play the fiddle and dance ♪

548
00:28:01,190 --> 00:28:03,190
♪ I'll send you home ♪

549
00:28:03,210 --> 00:28:05,690
♪ Since I met you that day ♪

550
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,510
♪ You are always in my mind ♪

551
00:28:07,870 --> 00:28:10,220
♪ Don't throw away ♪

552
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:12,150
♪ The roses I gave you in a hurry ♪

553
00:28:12,310 --> 00:28:14,220
♪ The roses I gave you ♪

554
00:28:14,530 --> 00:28:16,680
♪ The roses I gave you ♪

555
00:28:17,290 --> 00:28:33,780
♪ Come on, darling ♪

556
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:33,920
Three, two, one.

557
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,920
Alright, take a look. How is it?

558
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,220
It looks so beautiful.

559
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,000
It's because you are pretty.

560
00:28:44,510 --> 00:28:45,790
These figs'

561
00:28:46,830 --> 00:28:48,130
cultivation

562
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,750
depends on the saplings.

563
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:51,640
The older the sapling,

564
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,110
the tastier the figs.

565
00:28:53,370 --> 00:28:54,440
The small ones'

566
00:28:54,590 --> 00:28:55,740
figs aren't sweet.

567
00:28:56,090 --> 00:28:57,160
That young man

568
00:28:57,160 --> 00:28:58,050
knows nothing.

569
00:28:58,050 --> 00:28:59,420
Figs from small saplings

570
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,220
aren't sweet.

571
00:29:01,830 --> 00:29:03,230
I think it's quite sweet.

572
00:29:03,850 --> 00:29:05,510
You're making insinuations.

573
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:07,720
In recent years,

574
00:29:07,920 --> 00:29:08,920
businessmen

575
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:10,550
came to Kashgar's old town and left

576
00:29:10,550 --> 00:29:12,640
as they pleased.

577
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:14,640
A few of them have actually stayed.

578
00:29:15,330 --> 00:29:16,330
Just like the figs

579
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:17,550
growing on this tree, which fell,

580
00:29:17,550 --> 00:29:20,000
those men left without any hesitation.

581
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:20,940
Am I right?

582
00:29:34,830 --> 00:29:35,640
Xia Zi.

583
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,040
Look at me.

584
00:30:26,350 --> 00:30:27,130
Smash it.

585
00:30:32,650 --> 00:30:33,830
Smash it into pieces.

586
00:30:33,830 --> 00:30:34,440
Is this edible?

587
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:36,030
It is. Eat it.

588
00:30:39,850 --> 00:30:40,810
I think Uncle

589
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:42,140
won't agree so easily.

590
00:30:42,170 --> 00:30:43,430
Don't be so impatient.

591
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:46,240
I'm not impatient.

592
00:30:46,530 --> 00:30:48,730
I really want to run this homestay well.

593
00:30:49,070 --> 00:30:51,030
I'm doing business on my own.

594
00:30:51,220 --> 00:30:52,880
No one shares the risk with me.

595
00:30:54,380 --> 00:30:55,180
Don't worry.

596
00:30:55,930 --> 00:30:58,330
I will protect this century-old shop well.

597
00:30:58,590 --> 00:30:59,530
It's a win-win situation.

598
00:30:59,530 --> 00:31:00,330
No one loses.

599
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:03,700
Just like this fig,

600
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:06,570
we hit it off instantly.

601
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,210
That's not how you smash it.

602
00:31:14,030 --> 00:31:14,940
I will

603
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:17,510
try to convince my uncle.

604
00:31:17,740 --> 00:31:19,400
But I have one condition.

605
00:31:19,790 --> 00:31:20,570
Within five years,

606
00:31:20,570 --> 00:31:22,070
this homestay cannot be
transferred to anyone else.

607
00:31:22,070 --> 00:31:24,270
This must be written into the contract.

608
00:31:24,590 --> 00:31:26,420
Alright, I agree.

609
00:31:26,900 --> 00:31:28,810
Then I think our new homestay

610
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:31,010
can keep the carved wooden doors,

611
00:31:31,010 --> 00:31:33,460
and make it a folk culture photo spot.

612
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,120
Yeah, that's a good idea.

613
00:31:36,550 --> 00:31:38,680
Let me think about how to tell my uncle.

614
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:49,320
Come down quickly.

615
00:31:53,420 --> 00:31:54,450
Be careful.

616
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:00,000
Uncle.

617
00:32:00,140 --> 00:32:00,880
Tell me.

618
00:32:01,420 --> 00:32:02,330
At this moment,

619
00:32:02,330 --> 00:32:03,960
if someone suddenly jumped out

620
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,220
to play Tobok with you,

621
00:32:05,220 --> 00:32:06,220
what would you do?

622
00:32:07,880 --> 00:32:08,940
It's been a long time

623
00:32:08,940 --> 00:32:10,920
since I played this Tobok game.

624
00:32:11,180 --> 00:32:12,220
Besides,

625
00:32:12,450 --> 00:32:14,000
the person who played Tobok with me

626
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:15,440
is no longer here.

627
00:32:15,810 --> 00:32:16,570
No one knows

628
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:19,480
that my knucklebone is
in my pocket right now.

629
00:32:19,980 --> 00:32:20,980
But I know that

630
00:32:21,330 --> 00:32:21,830
I,

631
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,720
Xia Hui's daughter,

632
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:24,400
Xia Zi,

633
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:26,200
the homestay's goddaughter,

634
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:29,240
will officially take over
for my dad, Xia Hui,

635
00:32:29,330 --> 00:32:31,090
to play the game of Tobok with you.

636
00:32:31,090 --> 00:32:33,020
Please take out your knucklebone.

637
00:32:37,510 --> 00:32:38,510
My clothes are...

638
00:32:46,460 --> 00:32:48,080
I

639
00:32:48,530 --> 00:32:50,050
have been led astray

640
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:51,270
by you little kids.

641
00:32:51,390 --> 00:32:53,120
You guys are really something.

642
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:05,290
Open your hand

643
00:33:05,750 --> 00:33:07,550
and let me see your knucklebone.

644
00:33:08,070 --> 00:33:09,870
If I open my hand,

645
00:33:10,270 --> 00:33:12,090
and you do not have yours,

646
00:33:12,090 --> 00:33:13,440
you will lose to me.

647
00:33:17,110 --> 00:33:18,030
Uncle,

648
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:19,380
if you lose,

649
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:20,740
I don't want sheep

650
00:33:20,830 --> 00:33:21,720
or money.

651
00:33:22,010 --> 00:33:23,330
I want you to give me a chance.

652
00:33:23,330 --> 00:33:24,860
Give our homestay a chance.

653
00:33:39,980 --> 00:33:43,330
I know you are experienced at Tobok.

654
00:33:43,330 --> 00:33:45,010
If I let you lose to me so easily,

655
00:33:45,010 --> 00:33:45,940
it would be unfair to you.

656
00:33:45,940 --> 00:33:46,550
Let's do it another day.

657
00:33:46,550 --> 00:33:47,380
Arzugul.

658
00:34:07,940 --> 00:34:08,840
Uncle.

659
00:34:09,469 --> 00:34:10,800
I can't take it anymore.

660
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:12,170
I need water.

661
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:13,320
Water.

662
00:34:13,900 --> 00:34:14,920
You've only been buried for a short while.

663
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,260
Can't you take it?

664
00:34:19,770 --> 00:34:20,500
Uncle.

665
00:34:21,050 --> 00:34:22,400
What are you holding?

666
00:34:22,710 --> 00:34:25,389
This is the Tobok game we play.

667
00:34:25,420 --> 00:34:26,820
See this knucklebone?

668
00:34:27,760 --> 00:34:29,090
Arzugul's dad has one,

669
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,320
and I have one.

670
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:32,030
If I go to him and ask,

671
00:34:32,130 --> 00:34:33,170
"Where is your knucklebone?"

672
00:34:33,170 --> 00:34:34,480
and he can't take it out,

673
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:36,380
he has to compensate me with a sheep.

674
00:34:36,380 --> 00:34:38,010
If he asks me for them,

675
00:34:38,010 --> 00:34:38,860
and I can't take one out,

676
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:40,550
I have to give him a sheep.

677
00:34:40,860 --> 00:34:41,880
But nowadays,

678
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:43,190
these young guys

679
00:34:43,190 --> 00:34:44,170
don't

680
00:34:44,210 --> 00:34:45,540
play this game anymore.

681
00:34:48,110 --> 00:34:49,030
Alright.

682
00:34:49,290 --> 00:34:50,590
I see you can't take it anymore.

683
00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:52,190
After a few more sand therapies,

684
00:34:52,190 --> 00:34:53,860
all your illnesses will be gone.

685
00:34:53,860 --> 00:34:54,730
Come on.

686
00:34:54,730 --> 00:34:55,830
Let's go.

687
00:34:58,550 --> 00:35:00,000
Uncle, what's up?

688
00:35:00,030 --> 00:35:01,480
Slowly.

689
00:35:01,510 --> 00:35:02,420
Let's hurry back.

690
00:35:02,420 --> 00:35:03,920
Come on, take it easy.

691
00:35:04,300 --> 00:35:05,320
It burns.

692
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:18,240
Uncle, slow down.

693
00:35:21,210 --> 00:35:21,820
I'm fine.

694
00:35:23,070 --> 00:35:24,920
-What did the doctor say?
-So serious?

695
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,450
Why are you in a wheelchair?

696
00:35:26,460 --> 00:35:27,520
The bones are fine.

697
00:35:27,590 --> 00:35:28,920
Just a slight sprain.

698
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:30,850
Come on, son.

699
00:35:31,340 --> 00:35:33,140
Look how dirty your clothes are.

700
00:35:33,150 --> 00:35:33,910
Let me wash them for you.

701
00:35:33,910 --> 00:35:34,630
Uncle.

702
00:35:35,030 --> 00:35:37,440
Since the bones are fine,

703
00:35:38,530 --> 00:35:40,460
please take out your knucklebone.

704
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:43,840
Naughty girl.

705
00:35:44,330 --> 00:35:46,000
I'm already in a wheelchair.

706
00:35:46,110 --> 00:35:49,240
Are you still trying
to take advantage of my misfortune?

707
00:35:49,260 --> 00:35:50,590
When you played this game with my Dad,

708
00:35:50,590 --> 00:35:52,760
didn't you always take advantage of him?

709
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,240
I remember one year, there was a flood,

710
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:56,130
and my mom and I hid in a tree.

711
00:35:56,190 --> 00:35:58,320
You waded across the river to tell him,

712
00:35:58,780 --> 00:36:00,400
"Take out your knucklebone".

713
00:36:00,400 --> 00:36:01,000
Forgot it?

714
00:36:01,110 --> 00:36:02,530
That's how the game is played.

715
00:36:02,530 --> 00:36:03,190
Right.

716
00:36:03,190 --> 00:36:05,320
That's exactly how the game is played.

717
00:36:07,980 --> 00:36:10,850
You knew I changed
clothes in the hospital.

718
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:12,320
Here.

719
00:36:19,980 --> 00:36:20,810
Zhou.

720
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:31,450
I'm helping you.

721
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,610
Uncle gave it to me.

722
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,480
You cheated.

723
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:36,300
I was prepared for this.

724
00:36:36,300 --> 00:36:38,720
Before I went into the hospital,

725
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:40,570
I gave the knucklebone to Zhou.

726
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:41,150
Girl.

727
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:43,760
Now that your Dad is gone,

728
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:46,810
the game we played

729
00:36:46,830 --> 00:36:48,290
should also come to an end.

730
00:36:48,420 --> 00:36:49,460
I know why

731
00:36:49,460 --> 00:36:51,460
you wanted to play this game with me.

732
00:36:51,460 --> 00:36:52,320
Opportunities

733
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:55,040
can't be obtained by winning or losing.

734
00:36:55,100 --> 00:36:56,250
Time shows

735
00:36:56,550 --> 00:36:58,260
a person's true colors.

736
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,480
It can just be won by sincerity.

737
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:01,540
Do you understand?

738
00:37:04,220 --> 00:37:05,040
Do you two

739
00:37:05,070 --> 00:37:06,870
dare to play Tobok one more time?

740
00:37:08,190 --> 00:37:09,530
The only condition is

741
00:37:10,010 --> 00:37:11,420
to keep our inn

742
00:37:11,980 --> 00:37:12,960
and make it

743
00:37:13,170 --> 00:37:15,690
prosperous again.

744
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:22,810
To the beginning of our great friendship.

745
00:37:23,170 --> 00:37:25,500
To the beginning of our great friendship.

746
00:37:32,290 --> 00:37:33,690
Do you need an airport pickup?

747
00:37:33,690 --> 00:37:35,690
Okay, please send me the flight number.

748
00:37:35,690 --> 00:37:36,500
I'll arrange it later.

749
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:36,430
[Lobby manager]

750
00:37:37,220 --> 00:37:38,100
[Already placed an order]

751
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:48,840
Look, our family

752
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,420
also has a space like this.

753
00:37:50,420 --> 00:37:51,760
We can dance like this

754
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:52,730
in that space too.

755
00:37:52,730 --> 00:37:53,280
Right.

756
00:37:59,340 --> 00:37:59,900
This shop is the one I mentioned before.

757
00:37:59,900 --> 00:38:01,820
A room costs 1,500 yuan a night.

758
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,730
There are not many rooms,

759
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:06,020
but they are almost always fully booked.

760
00:38:06,030 --> 00:38:08,030
Just like ours, it has three floors.

761
00:38:11,540 --> 00:38:13,800
Uncle, look how booming the business is.

762
00:38:14,260 --> 00:38:15,320
Just a little bit of food

763
00:38:15,320 --> 00:38:16,390
costs 89 yuan?

764
00:38:16,420 --> 00:38:17,300
Uncle.

765
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:18,700
Keep your voice down.

766
00:38:18,820 --> 00:38:20,140
People are mainly paying
for the atmosphere

767
00:38:20,140 --> 00:38:21,340
and the environment.

768
00:38:21,630 --> 00:38:22,500
These few shops

769
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:25,050
are hard to book during the peak season.

770
00:38:25,050 --> 00:38:27,040
Prices are probably

771
00:38:27,090 --> 00:38:29,090
several or even over ten times ours.

772
00:38:29,230 --> 00:38:30,090
That's normal.

773
00:38:30,320 --> 00:38:31,250
Over ten times?

774
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:31,760
Yes.

775
00:38:31,780 --> 00:38:32,610
So expensive.

776
00:38:32,650 --> 00:38:33,530
Exactly.

777
00:38:33,850 --> 00:38:34,410
Uncle.

778
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:36,760
I think if we

779
00:38:36,760 --> 00:38:37,780
renovate our shop too,

780
00:38:37,780 --> 00:38:39,580
it could be this popular as well.

781
00:38:39,710 --> 00:38:42,480
We are living in the new Kashgar now.

782
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:45,630
That means having both heritage
and innovation.

783
00:38:46,770 --> 00:38:48,870
I'll redesign and renovate

784
00:38:48,900 --> 00:38:50,050
our home.

785
00:39:02,110 --> 00:39:04,170
You don't plan to return to Shanghai?

786
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:07,100
Yes.

787
00:39:07,530 --> 00:39:08,930
I plan to stay in Kashgar.

788
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:10,340
No, Xia Zi.

789
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:12,920
You have to go back to Shanghai.

790
00:39:14,290 --> 00:39:15,520
Maybe it's because

791
00:39:15,590 --> 00:39:17,920
I'm used to constantly chasing after you.

792
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:20,000
You got into a school in Shanghai,

793
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:21,670
and I joined the song and dance troupe.

794
00:39:21,670 --> 00:39:22,670
You bought a house,

795
00:39:22,670 --> 00:39:24,870
and I wanted to be the principal dancer.

796
00:39:26,010 --> 00:39:27,230
And now you're telling me

797
00:39:27,230 --> 00:39:28,570
you want to go back to Kashgar?

798
00:39:28,570 --> 00:39:29,660
Are you kidding me?

799
00:39:30,790 --> 00:39:32,250
What can you do here?

800
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:34,710
Just be Manager Xia forever?

801
00:39:34,940 --> 00:39:36,000
That's a good idea.

802
00:39:38,030 --> 00:39:39,380
Right now,

803
00:39:39,850 --> 00:39:42,180
I think I'm starting to like this feeling.

804
00:39:43,240 --> 00:39:44,240
The grain

805
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,540
and the weeds

806
00:39:45,650 --> 00:39:46,940
grew together.

807
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:51,470
Grain and weeds?

808
00:39:52,280 --> 00:39:52,880
All right.

809
00:40:19,930 --> 00:40:20,980
Minawar,

810
00:40:21,690 --> 00:40:23,690
you did a good job keeping it secret.

811
00:40:23,970 --> 00:40:26,130
If your mother-in-law hadn't
come to ask for a leave for you today,

812
00:40:26,130 --> 00:40:27,250
how long

813
00:40:27,590 --> 00:40:29,590
were you planning to hide it from us?

814
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:31,860
I...

815
00:40:32,190 --> 00:40:33,280
Having a baby is a good thing.

816
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,540
What are you afraid of?

817
00:40:36,260 --> 00:40:38,480
I wanted to tell you
after the performance.

818
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:39,410
That won't work.

819
00:40:39,660 --> 00:40:41,480
Your mother-in-law specially
came to tell us.

820
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:42,680
We can't be careless.

821
00:40:42,850 --> 00:40:43,550
How about this?

822
00:40:43,550 --> 00:40:44,570
From tomorrow onwards,

823
00:40:44,570 --> 00:40:45,830
work in the dressing room.

824
00:40:45,830 --> 00:40:47,060
The work there is lighter,

825
00:40:47,060 --> 00:40:48,660
which is good for both you and the baby.

826
00:40:48,660 --> 00:40:51,720
Let Gulistan be the leading actress
for the time being.

827
00:40:54,330 --> 00:40:56,270
How did they know you were pregnant?

828
00:40:56,270 --> 00:40:57,750
That's so disrespectful.

829
00:40:59,130 --> 00:40:59,610
Then,

830
00:41:00,750 --> 00:41:01,770
what about

831
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:03,050
Sänäm?

832
00:41:04,150 --> 00:41:05,810
Gulistan is playing the role.

833
00:41:07,320 --> 00:41:08,320
Why?

834
00:41:09,610 --> 00:41:11,610
They don't know that lately,

835
00:41:13,030 --> 00:41:14,650
I practiced Sänäm

836
00:41:16,370 --> 00:41:18,100
until my feet cramped.

837
00:41:19,670 --> 00:41:22,510
Every day, I longed to be Sänäm on stage.

838
00:41:28,300 --> 00:41:29,570
I am Sänäm.

839
00:41:30,980 --> 00:41:31,940
I have already

840
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:33,440
embodied Sänäm.

841
00:41:35,210 --> 00:41:37,010
No one is more like Sänäm than me.

842
00:41:44,690 --> 00:41:46,460
Do you want to see me dance?

843
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:51,530
Yes.
